==English==

===Adjective===
'''illegal'''

# {{law}} Contrary to or [[forbidden]] by law, usually [[criminal law|criminal]] rather than [[civil law]] (see [[unlawful]]).
# Not [[permitted]] by [[rule]]s, but not necessarily against the [[law]]. (''Moving a pawn backward is an '''illegal''' move in chess'')
#([[stamp-collecting]]) a totally [[fictitious]] [[issue]] printed for collectors, often issued on behalf of a non-existent territory or country.  Also known as [[bogus]].
====Antonyms====
*[[lawful]]
*[[legal]]

====Synonyms====
*[[criminal]]
*[[felonious]]
*[[illicit]]
*[[unlawful]]

====Translations====
*[[il·legal]]

===Noun===
'''illegal'''
# (slang) a person within a country (typically the United States) who is present in violation of the immigration laws.
* See also [[illegal alien]], [[mojado]] and [[wetback]].

===Derived terms===
*[[illegal alien]]

